msgid "The following files and parameters in the table can be used when a new account is created with the <command>useradd</command> command. Settings such as these are stored for each user account in the <filename>/etc/shadow</filename> file. If using the &yast; tool ( <guimenu>User and Group Management</guimenu> ) to add users, the settings are available on a per-user basis. Here are the various settings, some of which can also be system-wide (for example, modification of <filename>/etc/login.defs</filename> and <filename>/etc/default/useradd</filename> ):"
